<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO JOHN RATLIFF</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug 15  6:24:17 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
John,<br><br>
I apologize for some of my salty language. I think that you would agree that I have kept its usage to a minimum, and have included it (the f word) in order to show, intentionally, my frustration with the war.<br><br>
Racial slurs are something I left behind in Vietnam, and appreciate your sensitivities about them. You are right on the money. Used in any context they show disregard and disrespect.<br><br>
You are correct also about various writings becoming stereotypical of Vietnam vets, that is why it is necessary for some to interject differing points of view that tend to dispell these stereotypes.<br><br>
Thanks for your levelheadedness.<br><br>
Peace.
